Some phones don't support call recording or stop supporting it after update. Remove other call recording apps, reboot your phone and re-install ACR, set recording delay to 5 seconds and try again. 

If fails, try other Audio Sources like VOICE_COMMUNICATION or VOICE_RECOGNITION. 

Set to MIC if all fails and use call recording with speaker

content: automatic record on every call when enabled. Sound quality is good audio very clear on both ends of the call
Not saport
Been 4 months still not fixed and don't tell me to reinstall the app. I have over 200 conversations with one side recorded.
replyContent:
Your phone have "Power saving" or "Battery saver" options under Phone Settings. Open it and add ACR to "Protected apps". 

See https://bitbucket.org/copluk/acr/issues/607 for how to on few phones

Also, do not close recent apps and remove memory cleaning and battery saving apps if you have any

replyContent:
Unfortunately there is an issue with Android 7.1.1 that prevents call recording working reliably. Our latest update was able to fix this in few phones but not on all. Try restarting your phone and set recording delay to 5 seconds.

We are still working on it and hopefully Android 8 update will fix it very soon

content: One of the best recorder ed ever

This app works, incoming callers will be recorded alongside your voice and the app has lots of startup questions at setup methodically setting up the app properly. It works and it's more sophisticated than other apps and it has a lower rating but it's worth more than other apps. I bought it, well worth it.
Excellent just what I required. Well worth the money thanks.

Recordings are clear, included features are useful, design and layout are uncluttered and intuitive. Does what it says on the tin without fail. Paid for the pro version to encourage the developer to keep up the great work.  [Edit] Sometime after the above review I upgraded to a new phone: With my first year Google Pixel 1, due to a restriction with Android, ACR was unable to record internal audio. So I would use the speaker phone to get clear recordings of both sides of the conversation through the phones microphone. This app was just too useful to give up on. I'm glad I persisted.  Now with my new Google Pixel 2, ACR records the audio from phone calls without issues. The recordings are clear and it's easy to hear both sides of the conversation with or without the speaker phone on. I don't know whether this was a change from Android 8.1 or a change in ACR but I'm quite pleased with how this app works so well and reliably.  Kudos to the devs.
Does it support note 8? Can record only my side... :(

Set to MIC if all fails and use call recording with speaker
